content: The President will be in town... like him, or not (this is not a political post, it's an informational post)  This is a Mass Transit kind of day New Yorkers!  FDR will be shut for a while as they motorcade the President up the East side to midtown.  Avoid the 50's between 5th and 6th Avenues, then they'll motorcade over to the Intrepid for a dinner that starts around 7pm.  He'll leave NYC at around 9ish and fly to New Jersey where he'll be for the rest of the weekend.  Plan accordingly and use Mass Transit.  Please share this post for all of your friends to see. #abc7NY  Lori Stokes Ken Rosato Bill Evans Meteorologist

content: 22 people dead, 59 injured, after an apparent suicide bomber detonated a bomb following an Ariana Grande concert in the UK on Monday night.  Grande tweeted, "broken. from the bottom of my heart, i am so so sorry. i don't have words"  Families are still searching for their loved ones.  Dray Clark reported that some of the people who died may have been trampled by the crowd as they ran in a panic from the venue.  Candace Mccowan is in Times Square covering the added security and Josh Einiger is flying to Manchester to cover the story.   This is so incredibly difficult to digest, so many young innocent victims.  #abc7NY
name: Heather O'Rourke Traffic

content:
I'm a sucker for puppies!  These adorable furbabies were born to a mother who was abused with at staple gun  😥 Who could do such a thing??? The mom, Everley, has been trying so hard to take care of her eight pups, but one of them passed away. Unfortunately, Everley is too undernourished to nurse.  The cost of care is very expensive, so Ramapo-Bergen Animal Refuge is reaching out to supporters and others to please make a donation to the Betty Lou Medical Fund.  (Ramapo Bergen Animal Refuge, Inc. is a non-profit, no-kill shelter serving all of Northern New Jersey.)  #abc7NY
